# =============================================================================
# Social Events App — example environment variables (TEMPLATE — NO real secrets)
# =============================================================================
#
# HOW TO USE
#   Copy this file to `.env` (and the per-app templates to apps/*/.env*) and fill in
#   real values locally. Real `.env*` files are gitignored and MUST NOT be committed.
#   Only `*.example` templates are tracked in git.
#
# ENVIRONMENTS (APP_ENV / *_APP_ENV)
#   local       Developer machine. Local or branch Supabase, test data, sandboxed
#               analytics/crash/AI. No production secrets, ever.
#   staging     Pre-production mirror of production security/RLS. Separate Supabase
#               project + keys. Migrations land here before production.
#   production  Real closed-beta users. Separate project + keys. Access limited and
#               logged. Secrets managed outside git (CI / host secret store).
#
# NAMING CONVENTION — PUBLIC vs SERVER-ONLY (this is a safety boundary)
#   EXPO_PUBLIC_*   Bundled into the Expo / React Native client. PUBLIC ONLY.
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_*   Bundled into the Next.js browser build. PUBLIC ONLY.
#   (no prefix)     SERVER-ONLY. Never bundled into a client. Use only in Next.js
#                   server code / Edge Functions / CI.
#
# HARD SECURITY RULES (see /docs/05_ARCHITECTURE.md §8.2/§19, /docs/07_SECURITY_RLS.md §8)
#   - SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY is SERVER-SIDE ONLY. Never in the mobile app, never in
#     any browser/client bundle, never behind an EXPO_PUBLIC_/NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix.
#   - The mobile app may use ONLY anon-safe EXPO_PUBLIC_* values.
#   - Server-only variables must never use a public prefix.
#   - Never commit real credentials. Production secrets live outside git.
# =============================================================================

# --- App environment ---------------------------------------------------------
APP_ENV=local

# --- Mobile public config (safe to expose in the Expo client) ----------------
EXPO_PUBLIC_APP_ENV=local
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

# --- Admin public config (safe to expose in the Next.js browser) -------------
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_ENV=local
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

# --- Admin server-only (NEVER exposed to any client bundle) ------------------
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY bypasses RLS — server-side admin / Edge Functions only.
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=
ADMIN_ALLOWED_EMAILS=

# --- Analytics (PostHog) — not wired yet -------------------------------------
EXPO_PUBLIC_POSTHOG_KEY=
EXPO_PUBLIC_POSTHOG_HOST=
NEXT_PUBLIC_POSTHOG_KEY=
NEXT_PUBLIC_POSTHOG_HOST=

# --- Crash reporting (Sentry) — not wired yet --------------------------------
EXPO_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DSN=
NEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DSN=

# --- AI moderation (SERVER-ONLY) — not wired yet -----------------------------
# AI keys are server-only; never expose to a client. AI is assistive, not judge.
OPENAI_API_KEY=
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
